to the editor i agree that health aid for poor countries editorial jan 3 is a sound investment but my 35 years of experience in international development make clear that no single investment works by itself to succeed health spending must be buttressed by investments in education and income earning opportunities especially for girls and women closing the gender gap in education and earning capacity essential in its own right helps women care for their families research shows that employment and education of girls and women also help them avoid hiv aids unwanted pregnancy and early marriage adrienne germain president international women 's health coalition new york jan 3 2002

